'''Party of New Type (PNT)''' is a voluntary public association in Russia, formed on an informal basis of a common world outlook. It is not an officially registered party. S.Sulakshin is Chairman of the Party and one of the self-nominated candidates in [[2018 Russian Presidential Election|the 2018 Russian presidential election]]. == History of creation == In the scientific circulation the term "party of new type" was entered into by [[Lenin, V. I.|Vladmir Lenin]].{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}} In 2015, the General Director of the Center for Political Thought and Ideology, Stepan Sulakshin, announced the idea of creating PNT as opposition to [[Vladimir Putin]]'s governance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ng.ru/politics/2015-10-29/1_partia.html|title="Партия нового типа" ищет руководителя|publisher=}}</ref> The following year, he made a declaration of intent to create a "party of new type." Russian Prime Minister [[Dmitry Medvedev]] also used the phrase, in reference to the [[United Russia]] party: "The past election campaign marked the beginning of the most important stage for our Party - the formation of a new type of party." It is likely that the formulation was included in the speech of the prime minister by the efforts of the speechwriters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://er.ru/news/146613/|title=Медведев: «Единая Россия» находится на этапе формирования Партии нового типа|date=24 September 2016|publisher=}}</ref>
The founding congress of PNT was held on June 17, 2017. At the congress it was decided to create a party as a public association without registration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://neuromir.tv/uchreditelnyy-syezd-partii-novogo-tipa/|title=учредительный Съезд|publisher=}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://1pnt.ru/uchreditelnyy-syezd-pnt/uchred2017|title=Есть такая партия! Партия нового типа. ПНТ|website=1pnt.ru}}</ref> == Ideology == Sulakshin S. refused to call the party's agenda left-patriotic, explaining that it "has a universal program aimed at all citizens." PNT stands on the balanced political platform of a "solidary society" in which revolutions and expropriations will never again occur, but will be based on "work, justice and freedom."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ng.ru/politics/2017-09-29/1_7084_sulakshin.html|title=Конкуренцию Путину хочет составить еще один несистемный кандидат|publisher=}}</ref> == References == {{reflist}}
